hat it was like for these young men to grow up gay in an immigrant family, to be the one gay person in their school and ethnic community, and to be a person of color in predominantly White gay spaces. Brown and Gay in LA is an homage to second-generation gay men and their radical redefinition of what it means to be gay, to be a man, to be a person of color, and, ultimately, what it means to be an American.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aAcceptance.  aAsian American.  aBody.  aBullying.  aChildhood.  aClass.  aCollege.  aComing out.  aCommunity.  aCovering.  aCultural Centers.  aEducation.  aEthnicity.  aFamily.  aFilipino.  aGay.  aGayborhoods.  aGender.  aHigher Education.  aImmigration.  aIntersectionality.  aLGBTQ.  aLatino.  aMasculinity.  aQueer.  aRace.  aRacism.  aReligion.  aRespectability.  aSexualities.  aSexuality.  aSizeism.  aSocial Media.  aStudent Organizations.  aTherapy.  aTransgender.  aTransnational.  aUrban.  aWhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075162840uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479806614.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479806614423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479806614/original  a978-3-11-075162-8  New York University Press